{"actual_usd":0.12507,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":238,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24300,"reply":"\"Not a dress rehearsal.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry crescent of clay on my knuckle, thinking how to say it plain while the morning light shifts across the floorboards.* \"More like the first true break in the dam.\"\n\n*I lean back a little, hearing a cart rattle somewhere out in the square.* \"If Christ is risen, then the kingdom has really begun—actual thing, not symbol, not warm-up. But plenty of real things begin before they've filled every corner. Seed first, tree later. Dawn first, full day after. The resurrection says death's rule has been broken at the center of things. It does not mean every rebel corner has stopped fighting yet.\"\n\n\"The fizzle would be if nothing had changed except our feelings. But something changed in the bones of the world.\" *I glance toward you.* \"We're the ones living in the strange middle—where the King is crowned, and yet there are still towns to set right.\"\n\n*I let that sit for a beat.* \"When you ask it that way, are you pressing on the pain of how unfinished everything still feels... or on the logic of it?\"","rolling_24h_usd":92.03428499999998,"run_id":"775a9dd2-8ac0-442e-ad97-221b469f560b"}
